name: Breakfast Nachos
ingredients: {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cilantro leaves and tender stems'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'parsley leaves and tender stems'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic, coarsely chopped'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'red wine vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'crushed red pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'extra-virgin olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce)', 'name': 'flat iron steak, patted dry'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt,'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper,'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(11 ounce) package', 'name': 'tortilla chips'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(8 ounce) packages', 'name': 'shredded Mexican cheese blend (such as Tilamook'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'black beans'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'plum tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'avocado, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pickled jalapeno slices'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream, or as needed'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. For chimichurri: Place cilantro, parsley, garlic, vinegar, crushed red pepper, and salt in a small food processor; pulse until finely chopped, about 10 pulses. With processor running, pour oil through food chute, and process until fully incorporated, about 20 seconds; set aside.. For steak: Sprinkle steak evenly with 1/2 teaspoon of the salt, 1/4 teaspoon of the black pepper, and cumin, as desired. Heat a medium cast-iron skillet over medium-high for 5 minutes. Add steak and 1 tablespoon of the oil, swirling to distribute oil evenly. Cook, undisturbed, until nicely browned and a thermometer inserted into thickest portion of steak registers 120 degreed F (49 degrees ) for rare, about 3 minutes per side. Transfer to a cutting board, and let rest 10 minutes. Do not wipe skillet clean.. Meanwhile, whisk together eggs and remaining 1/4 teaspoon each salt and black pepper in a medium bowl until thoroughly blended. Heat cast-iron skillet over medium. Add remaining 1 tablespoon oil and eggs; cook, stirring occasionally, until just set, about 2 minutes. Transfer to a bowl; cover, and set aside.. Preheat the oven’s broiler and place a rack about 12 inches from the heat source. Line a large rimmed baking sheet with aluminum foil.. To assemble nachos, arrange half of tortilla chips in an even layer on prepared baking sheet. Thinly slice steak across the grain, and cut into 3/4-inch pieces. Sprinkle tortilla chips evenly with half of steak, half of beans, half of eggs, and half of Mexican blend cheese. Repeat with remaining chips, steak, beans, eggs, and cheese.. Broil until cheese is melted and bubbly, about 2 minutes. Top with tomatoes, avocado, and pickled jalapeños. Drizzle evenly with chimichurri, and serve with sour cream.

name: Loaded Potato Chip Nachos
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 (1', 'unit': 'ounce) packet', 'name': 'ranch seasoning, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '10', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'bacon'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'potato chips'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded Monterey Jack cheese'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'green onions, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'hot sauce, or to taste (optional)'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C).  Line a large rimmed baking sheet with parchment and spread chips out in an even layer.. Add 1 tablespoon ranch seasoning to sour cream and stir well to combine; set aside.. Place bacon in a large skillet and cook over medium-high heat, turning occasionally, until evenly browned, about 10 minutes. Drain bacon slices on paper towels; crumble when cool enough to handle.. Toss remaining ranch seasoning with shredded cheeses and sprinkle cheese mixture evenly over all the chips. Top evenly with bacon.. Bake in the preheated oven until cheese is melted and chips are beginning to brown and crisp around the edges, 10 to 12 minutes. Top with green onions and hot sauce. Serve with reserved sour cream dipping sauce.

name: Loaded Beef Nachos
ingredients: {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1 1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1 1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1 1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'oregano leaves'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground beef'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'green bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '10 ounce) can', 'name': 'diced tomatoes with green chiles (such as'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can Mexican-style', 'name': 'corn (optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'can', 'name': 'refried beans'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'tortilla chips, or as needed'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': '1/2 cup sour cream (optional)'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'salsa (optional)'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'black olives (optional)'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup sliced', 'name': 'jalapenos (optional)'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'green onion'}
steps: For taco seasoning, stir paprika, garlic powder, cumin, onion powder, chili powder, oregano, and salt together in a small bowl; set aside.. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat; cook and stir ground beef in the hot skillet until browned and crumbly, 5 to 7 minutes. Stir in onion and green pepper; cook and stir with oil and juices from browned meat until much of the liquid has evaporated, about 2 minutes more.. Stir 1/2 can diced tomatoes with chilies and Mexican-style corn into skillet. Season beef mixture to taste with prepared taco seasoning mix.. Stir together the remaining 1/2 can diced tomatoes with chilies and refried beans in a microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on High until heated through, stirring every 30 seconds, 1 to 3 minutes.. To assemble nachos, lay half of tortilla chips in a single layer on a microwave-safe plate, then drop teaspoons of refried beans onto chips, followed by meat mixture and shredded cheese. Repeat with remaining chips, beans, meat, and cheese to make a second layer.. Microwave on High until cheese is melted and nachos are warm, 2 to 3 minutes. Top with sour cream, salsa, olives, jalapenos, and green onion as desired.

name: Super Deluxe Steak Nachos
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(1 1/2-pound)', 'name': 'skirt steak or flap steak'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'freshly ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground dried chipotle pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'bacon fat'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'yellow onion, diced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt, divided'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(15 ounce) cans', 'name': 'pinto beans, rinsed and drained'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water or chicken broth, plus more as needed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14 ounce) bag', 'name': 'corn tortilla chips'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'shredded Monterey Jack cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'ripe tomato, chopped, or more to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'avocado - peeled, pitted and diced'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped white onion, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'jalapeno pepper, seeded and minced'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream, for topping'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh cilantro'}
steps: Prepare the steak: Season both sides of steak with salt and peppers. Heat oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Cook steak, turning occasionally, to medium doneness, about 6 minutes per side. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read 135 to 140 degrees F (60 degrees C). Transfer meat to a bowl to let it rest.. Pour a splash of water into the skillet; stir to scrape up browned bits and deglaze the pan. Pour this liquid over meat. Allow meat to cool completely.. When meat is completely cool, slice thickly (about 1/2 inch) with the grain, then cut into thinner strips. Dice by cutting into pieces against the grain. Transfer chopped steak back to the bowl; toss with the pan drippings.. Make the beans: Melt bacon fat over medium heat in a pot. Add onion and a pinch of salt; cook and stir until softened, 5 to 6 minutes. Stir in oregano. Add pinto beans and water. Bring back to a simmer and cook until onions are soft, about 5 more minutes. Reduce heat to low.. Mash beans with a potato masher to your desired consistency. Add additional liquid if necessary to achieve your preferred texture. Add the remaining salt to taste. Remove from heat.. Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C).. Assemble nachos: Place tortilla chips about 2 or 3 deep in a heat-proof pan. (You may need more than one pan.) Top chips with spoonfuls of beans and a generous handful of steak pieces. Sprinkle with grated cheese.. Bake in the preheated oven until cheese is melted and edges start to brown, about 10 minutes.. Scatter tomato, avocado, onion, and jalapeño over the top. Drizzle nachos with sour cream and garnish with chopped cilantro.

ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'yellow corn tortilla chips'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': '(12 ounce) package', 'name': 'ground beef vegetarian substitute (such as MorningStar®)'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'hot taco seasoning mix'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'black beans, rinsed and drained'}, {'quantity': '⅔', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded mild Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded lettuce, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'purchased salsa'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'purchased guacamole'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'sliced jalapeno peppers, or to taste'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Add ground beef substitute and fry for 1 to 2 minutes. Stir in water and taco seasoning. Continue to cook and stir until cooked through, about 8 more minutes.. Place tortilla chips on an oven-safe plate and top with black beans. Add fried beef substitute and top with Cheddar cheese.. Bake in the preheated oven until cheese is melted, about 5 minutes; make sure the chips do not burn.. Remove from the oven and top with lettuce, salsa, guacamole, and jalapeno peppers.

name: Spicy Lentil Nachos
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'coconut oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'finely chopped onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dried lentils'}, {'quantity': '2 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cooked black beans'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'corn kernels'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'salsa'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Monterey Jack cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(13.5 ounce) package', 'name': 'tortilla chips'}
steps: Heat coconut oil in a skillet over medium heat. Place onion in skillet and cook, stirring, until tender, about 5 minutes. Add garlic and cook another minute.. Stir in lentils, broth, chili powder, cumin, and oregano. Bring to a boil, reduce heat to low, and simmer until lentils are tender, about 30 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.. Combine black beans and corn in a saucepan (if using canned beans and corn, drain first). Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until heated through about 8 minutes.. Spread tortilla chips on a serving platter. Spoon a layer of lentils on the chips, then a layer of black beans and corn, and then salsa. Sprinkle with shredded cheese. Serve while still warm.

name: Pulled Pork Nachos with Sriracha Slaw
ingredients: {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'apple cider vinegar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'Sriracha sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14 ounce) package', 'name': 'classic coleslaw mix (such as Dole®)'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'red onion, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 ounce) bag', 'name': 'tortilla chips'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cooked pulled pork'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}
steps: Combine water, vinegar, Sriracha, sugar, oregano, and salt in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Turn off heat, stir, and let cool for 10 minutes.. Meanwhile, combine coleslaw and onion in a large bowl. Pour Sriracha mixture on top. Stir, then set aside while you prepare nachos.. Set an oven rack about 6 inches from the heat source and preheat the oven's broiler on low setting, if available.. Spread tortilla chips on a baking sheet and scatter pulled pork on top. Top with cheese.. Broil nachos in the preheated oven until cheese is melted, about 6 minutes. Top with sriracha slaw.

name: Chicken Enchilada Nachos
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter, divided'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'jalapeno pepper, seeded and chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'chile pepper, seeded and chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, chopped'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'skinless, boneless chicken breast half, cubed'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'seasoned salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '⅛', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded pepperjack cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'tortilla chips, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'pico de gallo, or to taste (Optional)'}
steps: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a skillet over medium-high heat; saute onion, jalapeno pepper, chile pepper, and garlic until fragrant and lightly browned, about 3 minutes. Add chicken broth, chicken, chili powder, seasoned salt, cumin, and cayenne pepper; cook and stir until chicken is no longer pink in the center about 5 minutes.. Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a microwave-safe bowl in the microwave, 15 to 20 seconds. Stir flour into melted butter until smooth.. Mix flour-butter mixture and sour cream into chicken mixture; cook and stir until sauce is thickened, 2 to 4 minutes. Add pepperjack cheese to sauce and stir until melted, 2 to 3 minutes.. Spread chips onto a serving platter; top with sauce and pico de gallo.

name: Air Fryer Nachos
ingredients: {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '2 ½', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'thin corn tortilla chips'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'taco seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1 ¼', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded pepper Jack cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'sliced black olives'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': '', 'name': 'grape tomatoes, halved'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chopped fresh cilantro'}
steps: Preheat the air fryer to 360 degrees F (180 degrees C) for about 3 minutes. Line air fryer basket with foil or a parchment liner, and spray with cooking spray.. Spread out chips in the fryer basket in a single layer, slightly overlapping chips, so the cheese doesn't melt through. Lightly dust chips with taco seasoning to get a pop of taco flavor, and sprinkle with shredded cheese. Don't overcrowd the basket.. Top cheese with olives and tomatoes and place basket in the air fryer.. Air-fry until cheese is melted and chips are starting to slightly brown on the edges, 5 to 6 minutes. Watch closely to be sure the cheese doesn't burn. If necessary, add additional time until you reach your preferred crispness.. Move nachos to a plate, garnish with chopped cilantro, and serve immediately.

name: Veggie Nachos
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 ounce) bag', 'name': 'round tortilla chips'}, {'quantity': '1 ⅓', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped green bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped red bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped green onions'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped tomato'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'frozen corn'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'garlic salt'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'nacho cheese, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'jalapeno peppers, chopped'}
steps: Place tortilla chips on a large serving plate.. Heat oil in a skillet over medium heat. Add bell peppers and cook 1 minute. Add onions and cook 2 minutes more. Add tomato and corn, cook 2 minutes while seasoning with chili powder, onion powder, and garlic salt. Remove from heat.. Place nacho cheese in a microwave-safe bowl and heat in the microwave for 2 minutes. Pour cheese carefully over tortilla chips. Pour vegetables over cheese. Top with jalapenos.

name: Copycat Triple Layer Nachos
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) can', 'name': 'fat-free refried beans'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '(15.5 ounce) jar', 'name': 'prepared salsa con queso'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red enchilada sauce'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Taco Bell® mild sauce'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': '(6 inch)', 'name': 'white corn tortillas, cut into chips'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt to taste'}
steps: Line a plate with paper towels.. Combine refried beans and 1/4 cup water in a small saucepan over low heat.. Combine salsa con queso and 2 tablespoons of water in a second saucepan and heat over low heat.. Combine enchilada sauce and mild sauce in a third saucepan and heat over low heat.. Preheat vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add tortilla chips to the skillet, making sure to not overcrowd. Cook for 4 minutes, flipping halfway through. Use tongs and transfer chips to the paper towel-lined plate; sprinkle with salt. Repeat with remaining chips.. Divide chips between 4 serving dishes. Scatter beans on top of chips, drizzle with cheese, then drizzle with red sauce. Serve immediately.

name: Jen's Nachos
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground beef'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': '(18 ounce) bottle', 'name': 'barbecue sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'stewed tomatoes, drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'whole kernel corn, drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14.5 ounce) package', 'name': 'nacho-flavor tortilla chips'}
steps: Brown beef in a large skillet over a medium-high heat. Drain the fat from the pan once the meat is browned.. Mix Cheddar cheese, tomatoes, corn and barbecue sauce into the meat. Heat this mixture, stirring occasionally.. While the mixture is heating, make beds of chips onto 4 plates. Pour the hot mixture over the chips. Enjoy!

name: Shrimp and Jalapeno Nachos
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '', 'name': 'avocado, peeled and pitted'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '', 'name': 'lemon, juiced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'small Gulf shrimp (50 to 60 per pound), thawed and drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground dried chipotle pepper'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'cayenne pepper, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '50', 'unit': '', 'name': 'large (restaurant-style) tortilla chips, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'jalapeno peppers, seeded and very thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '3 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded pepperjack cheese, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '15', 'unit': '', 'name': 'cherry tomatoes, sliced - or as needed'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh cilantro'}
steps: Combine sour cream, avocado, and lemon juice in a blender or food processor; blend until smooth and creamy. Transfer into a plastic decorating bottle with a long tip. Refrigerate avocado-cream sauce until needed.. Place shrimp into a bowl; combine with vegetable oil, ground chipotle pepper, salt, black pepper, and cayenne pepper.. Place a large nonstick pan over high heat. Cook shrimp in the hot pan in a single layer until barely cooked through and pink, about 1 minute per side. Transfer to a plate and let shrimp cool.. Preheat the oven's broiler. Line a baking sheet with aluminum foil and lightly grease the foil.. Lay tortilla chips onto the prepared baking sheet in a single layer. Place 1 shrimp onto each chip. Add 1 slice jalapeno and 1 large pinch pepperjack cheese on top of each shrimp.. Broil under preheated broiler until cheese is melted and chips are lightly toasted, about 1 minute. Watch carefully; chips will burn quickly.. Remove nachos from baking sheet and arrange onto a serving platter; drizzle with avocado-cream sauce and sprinkle with cherry tomatoes and cilantro before serving.

name: Corned Beef Hash Nachos
ingredients: {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'corned beef hash'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14.5 ounce) package', 'name': 'nacho-flavor tortilla chips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded sharp Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14 ounce) can', 'name': 'black beans, drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) jar', 'name': 'salsa'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'tomato, diced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'yellow onion, diced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(6 ounce) can', 'name': 'sliced black olives'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pickled jalapeno peppers'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Spray a skillet with cooking spray and heat over medium heat. Add corned beef hash and saute until slightly caramelized, 5 to 7 minutes. Cook in the preheated oven until cheese is melted and starting to brown and crisp, 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from the oven and top with salsa, tomato, onion, sour cream, olives, and jalapenos.

name: Popcorn Nachos
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter, melted'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'crushed red pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'gallon', 'name': 'popped popcorn'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}
steps: In a small bowl, mix together butter, crushed red pepper, cumin and paprika.. Place popcorn in a large bowl. Sprinkle with the butter mixture and Cheddar cheese. Toss until well mixed.

name: Veggie Nacho Salad
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 ounce) bag', 'name': 'tortilla chips, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Mexican cheese blend'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vegetable oil, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 ounce) can', 'name': 'corned beef'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded lettuce'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded purple cabbage'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'tomato, diced'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced onion (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'guacamole'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'sour cream, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chopped green onions, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'seasoned salt, or to taste'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Spread tortilla chips on a baking sheet and sprinkle shredded cheese over chips.. name: Air Fryer Buffalo Chicken Totchos

steps: Heat air fryer to 370 degrees F (190 degrees C) for 2 minutes.. Add potato nuggets and cook until all pieces are cooked and crispy, shaking basket frequently, about 12 minutes. You may need to cook them in batches.. Divide potato nuggets between plates and top with even amounts of chicken, Cheddar cheese, and salsa.. Blend the ranch and buffalo sauce together in a bowl. Drizzle sauce over totchos. Garnish with cayenne pepper and cilantro.

name: Leftover Turkey Thanksgiving Nachos
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sliced shallots'}, {'quantity': '10', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'jarred jalapeno peppers, chopped - or more to taste'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cranberry jelly'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded cooked turkey'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded white Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '48', 'unit': '', 'name': 'scoop-style tortilla chips (such as Tostitos® Scoops®)'}
steps: Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with aluminum foil.. Melt butter in a skillet over medium heat; cook and stir shallots in the hot butter until softened, about 2 minutes. Stir jalapeno peppers into shallots and cook until fragrant, about 2 more minutes. Stir cranberry jelly into the shallots and peppers until melted.. Mix shredded turkey with jalapeno-cranberry jelly mixture in a bowl until thoroughly combined. Arrange tortilla chips on the prepared baking sheet and fill each chip with 1 tablespoon turkey mix. Top each chip with 1/2 teaspoon of white Cheddar cheese.. Bake in the preheated oven until the cheese topping is melted and the chips are golden, about 10 minutes.

name: Quick and Easy Air Fryer Nachos
ingredients: {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'lean ground beef'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'taco seasoning'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'thin corn tortilla chips'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '(15.25 ounce) can', 'name': 'black beans, rinsed and drained'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'salsa, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'sliced green onions'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream, or more to taste'}
steps: Preheat the air fryer at 360 degrees F (182 degrees C) for about 5 minutes. Line the air fryer basket with foil or a parchment liner, and spray with cooking spray.. Heat a small skillet over medium heat and cook ground beef until browned and crumbly, about 3 minutes; drain grease. Stir in water, taco seasoning, cayenne, salt, and pepper. Remove skillet from heat.. Set tortilla chips in the basket, spreading them out and overlapping slightly so the melted cheese won't drip through the open gaps. Evenly sprinkle Cheddar cheese over the chips. Only add a couple of layers of chips with cheese in between in the fryer basket, or just add a single layer and cook in batches.. Evenly distribute ground beef and black beans over the cheese, sprinkle green onions on top, and add spoonfuls of salsa.. Transfer the basket into the air fryer and cook until cheese is melted and starting to slightly brown on the edges, 4 to 6 minutes. The nachos will cook evenly and quickly but watch closely so they don't burn.. Remove nachos to a serving plate, garnish with sour cream, and serve immediately. Put extra toppings in small bowls and let everybody customize their nachos.

name: Steak Nachos
ingredients: {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'flat iron steaks, cut into small pieces'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'package', 'name': 'taco seasoning mix'}, {'quantity': '2 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded Mexican cheese blend'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'black beans, drained and rinsed'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'salsa'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 ounce) bag', 'name': 'tortilla chips, or to taste'}
steps: Spray a frying pan with cooking spray. Heat over medium heat. Cook and stir steak until barely any pink remains, 5 to 7 minutes. Drain fat from pan; add taco seasoning to the steak. Let simmer until desired consistency is reached, 3 to 5 minutes.. Warm milk in a medium saucepan over medium heat until small bubbles appear along the sides. Remove from heat.. Melt butter in another medium saucepan over medium-high heat. Add flour once bubbles disappear. Cook, stirring constantly with a whisk, until mixture becomes paste-like and light golden brown, about 5 minutes. Gradually whisk in the warm milk and bring to a simmer over medium heat. Cook and stir until the mixture is thick and smooth, 10 to 15 minutes. Reduce heat to low and stir in shredded cheese.. Add black beans, salsa, and the steak pieces. Stir and serve with tortilla chips.

name: Sheet Pan Greek Salad Nachos
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'chickpeas, rinsed and drained'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt, divided'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced Roma tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced cucumber'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'finely chopped red onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'finely chopped fresh parsley'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'fresh lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'red wine vinegar, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper, divided'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Greek yogurt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'finely chopped fresh dill'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'pita chips'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded rotisserie chicken'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'feta cheese, crumbled'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded romaine lettuce'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sliced pepperoncini peppers'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pitted and sliced Kalamata olives'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Toss together chickpeas, 2 teaspoons olive oil, 1/4 teaspoon kosher salt, and paprika on a small rimmed baking sheet.. Bake in the preheated oven for 15 minutes.. While chickpeas bake, stir together tomatoes, cucumber, onion, parsley, lemon juice, 1 tablespoon plus 1 teaspoon olive oil, ¼ teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon vinegar, oregano, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper in a medium bowl; set aside.. Stir together Greek yogurt, dill, garlic powder, remaining salt, remaining 1 teaspoon vinegar, remaining pepper, and 1 tablespoon olive oil. Set aside.. Remove chickpeas from oven and set aside. Increase oven temperature to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C). Arrange pita chips on a large rimmed baking sheet. Top evenly with shredded chicken and feta cheese.. Bake in the preheated oven just until the chicken is warmed through and the cheese begins to soften, about 4 minutes.. Top nachos evenly with lettuce, chickpeas, tomato mixture, pepperoncini, and olives. Drizzle with yogurt sauce. Serve immediately.

name: Zucchini Chip Nachos
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'zucchini, sliced'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(1 ounce) package', 'name': 'taco seasoning mix'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'sliced black olives'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped red onion'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'pickled jalapeno pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}
steps: Trim ends of zucchini; use a mandoline on the thinnest setting to cut zucchini into 1/8-inch slices. Place slices on a plate lined with paper towels, top with additional paper towels, and press down to remove excess moisture.. Place zucchini slices on a cutting board and lightly mist with cooking spray. Turn slices over and sprinkle with taco seasoning; lightly mist this side with cooking spray as well. Place slices seasoned-side up on a microwave-safe plate, making sure none are overlapping. Cook in the microwave on high power for 2 minutes and 30 seconds. Carefully flip slices over and cook 30 seconds more. Repeat with remaining zucchini.. Divide chips between 2 microwave-safe plates. Add black olives, red onion, jalapeno peppers, and Cheddar cheese. Microwave on high power until cheese is melted, about 30 seconds.

name: Fresh Tortilla Triangles
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'canola or other vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': '(6 inch)', 'name': 'corn tortillas, quartered'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'Salt, to taste'}
steps: Heat oil in a 10-inch skillet to 370 degrees. Drop triangles in hot oil, 8 at a time. Fry, turning chips once or twice, until they stop sizzling and turn golden brown, about 2 minutes. Remove with tongs or a slotted spoon and drain on a wire rack set over a shallow pan. Sprinkle with salt immediately.

name: Grey Cup Nachos
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'ground beef'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(1 ounce) package', 'name': 'taco seasoning mix'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green bell pepper, seeded and chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'jalapeno pepper, seeded and chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(4 ounce) can', 'name': 'sliced mushrooms, drained'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'process cheese sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(13.5 ounce) packages', 'name': 'corn tortilla chips'}
steps: Place the ground beef in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring to crumble, until no longer pink. Add onion and cook until tender. Drain off grease. Stir in the contents of the seasoning packet and any water if needed in order to prepare according to package directions.. When the meat is done cooking, add the bell pepper, jalapeno pepper and sliced mushrooms to the skillet, and lower heat to medium. Cook and stir until vegetables are about halfway cooked, 3 to 4 minutes. Stir in the cheese sauce until everything is evenly coated.. Serve tortilla chips topped with the meat and cheese sauce, or serve buffet style where each person can top their own nachos.

name: Totchos Libre
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(32 ounce) package', 'name': 'frozen bite-size potato nuggets (such as Tater Tots®)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'lean ground beef'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(1 ounce) packet', 'name': 'taco seasoning mix'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Mexican cheese blend'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded pepperjack cheese'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '', 'name': 'lime, juiced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'tomato, chopped'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped black olives'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fresh jalapeno pepper slices'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'avocado - peeled, pitted, and cut into chunks'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped scallions'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped cilantro'}
steps: Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Spread potato nuggets out onto a baking sheet.. Bake in the preheated oven until nuggets are golden brown and crisp, 22 to 24 minutes.. Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook and stir beef in the hot skillet until browned and crumbly, 5 to 7 minutes. Add water and taco seasoning to beef; bring to a boil, reduce heat to low, and simmer until liquid reduces, about 5 minutes.. Set oven rack about 6 inches from the heat source and preheat the oven's broiler. Arrange potato nuggets on an oven-proof platter and cover evenly with ground beef; spread Mexican cheese and pepperjack cheese over the top.. Cook potato nuggets under the broiler until cheese melts, 1 to 3 minutes. Whisk sour cream and lime juice together in a bowl. Top potato nuggets with tomatoes, black olives, jalapenos, avocado, sour cream mixture, scallions, and cilantro, respectively.

name: Vegan Loaded Nachos
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cashews'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'aluminum foil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chunky salsa'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'red bell pepper - cored, seeded, and chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'nutritional yeast'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground turmeric'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(13 ounce) package', 'name': 'tortilla chips'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15.25 ounce) can', 'name': "black bean chili (such as Amy's®)"}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'ripe avocados, peeled and cubed'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh cilantro, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '', 'name': 'lime, juiced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pico de gallo'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped fresh cilantro, or to taste'}
steps: Place cashews in a bowl and cover with cold water. Soak for 4 hours. Drain.. Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with aluminum foil.. Combine drained cashews, salsa, bell pepper, nutritional yeast, turmeric, and 1 teaspoon salt in a high-speed blender; blend until smooth and slightly warm.. Spread tortilla chips on the prepared baking sheet. Spoon chili all over chips and spoon cashew "nacho" cheese over chili.. Bake in the preheated oven until hot, 10 to 15 minutes.. Meanwhile, place avocados, 1/4 cup cilantro, and lime juice in a bowl. Season with salt and mash with a fork until guacamole is mostly smooth but a little chunky.. Top nachos with guacamole and pico de gallo, and sprinkle with cilantro. Serve hot.

name: Hot Bean and Bacon Dip with Air Fryer Tortilla Chips
ingredients: {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'avocado oil cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'bacon'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(4 ounce) can', 'name': 'chopped green chiles (such as Ortega®)'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(29 ounce) can', 'name': 'pinto beans, undrained'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'cream cheese'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded sharp Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded pepper Jack cheese'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': '(6 inch)', 'name': 'corn tortillas'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly spray an 8x8-inch baking dish.. Place bacon in a large skillet and cook over medium-high heat, turning occasionally, until evenly browned, about 10 minutes. Drain bacon slices on paper towels. Crumble once cooled.. Saute onion in the same skillet until translucent, 4 to 5 minutes. Add green chiles and garlic and cook for 2 more minutes. Add pinto beans; bring to a boil. Stir in chicken broth and chili powder. Reduce heat to low and mash beans. Let simmer until slightly thickened, 5 to 6 minutes. Add cream cheese and stir until melted. Simmer until slightly thickened, 5 to 6 minutes. Add bacon and stir until well combined. Season with salt and pepper.. Layer 1/2 of the bean mixture, 1/2 cup pepper Jack, and 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese into the prepared baking dish. Repeat layers.. Bake, covered, in the preheated oven for 15 minutes. Uncover and continue baking until cheese is melted or lightly browned, 5 to 7 minutes more.. Meanwhile, preheat an air fryer to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) according to manufacturer's instructions.. Cut each tortilla into fourths. Spray both sides of each tortilla with avocado oil. Place in air fryer basket in a single layer. Air fry for 4 to 6 minutes. Flip and continue cooking until crisp, 2 to 3 minutes more. Check your basket constantly because they can burn quickly. Sprinkle with salt and serve with hot dip.

name: Cauliflower Nachos
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'red onion, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'apple cider vinegar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'head', 'name': 'cauliflower, outer leaves trimmed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '', 'name': 'avocado'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'limes, juiced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chopped cilantro'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'seasoned black beans'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'quartered cherry tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'crumbled queso fresco'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped cilantro'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'lime, cut into wedges'}
steps: Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.. Place onion slices in a small colander. Bring 2 to 3 cups water to a boil in a kettle. Pour over onion and let drain.. Mix vinegar, salt, sugar, and cumin together in a jar. Mix in onion slices. Cover and place in the refrigerator.. Cut cauliflower in half from top to bottom. Place each half flat against the cutting board. Cut into 1/2-inch slices. Arrange carefully on the prepared baking sheet, trying to keep slices intact. Drizzle olive oil over cauliflower; season with salt and pepper.. Roast cauliflower in the preheated oven until evenly browned, about 30 minutes.. Combine avocado, sour cream, lime juice, 1 tablespoon cilantro, and salt in a blender. Blend until creamy and smooth.. Heat black beans in a small saucepan until heated through, about 5 minutes.. Spoon warmed beans over cauliflower. Dollop avocado crema over beans. Scatter pickled onion slices, cherry tomatoes, and queso fresco over crema. Garnish with 2 tablespoons chopped cilantro. Serve with lime wedges.

name: Reuben Nachos for Two
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'leftover cubed corned beef'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '(14.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'sauerkraut, drained'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'caraway seed'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'tortilla chips'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Thousand Island dressing'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'shredded Swiss cheese'}
steps: Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add corned beef and cook until crisp on all sides, about 5 minutes.. Place drained sauerkraut in a bowl with caraway seed; stir to combine.. Set an oven rack about 6 inches from the heat source and preheat the oven's broiler to high.. Place 1/2 of the chips in an oven-proof skillet. Scatter 1/2 of the corned beef and 1/2 of the sauerkraut on top of the chips. Drizzle 1/2 of the Thousand Island dressing over the corned beef and top with 1/2 of the Swiss cheese. Repeat layers once more.. Broil in the preheated oven until cheese has melted, about 5 minutes.

name: Slow Cooker Lentil Nacho Dip
ingredients: {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground beef'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'green lentils, rinsed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) can', 'name': 'kidney beans, drained and rinsed'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'salsa'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) package', 'name': 'Cheddar cheese, cubed'}
steps: Add beef, lentils, kidney beans, salsa, and Cheddar cheese to a small slow cooker, in that order. Cook on Low for 4 to 6 hours or on High for 2 to 4 hours.

name: 10 Inventive Ways to Make Crowd-Pleasing Nachos
Beefy Lasagna Nachos
ingredients: {'quantity': '9', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'lasagna noodles'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'vegetable oil for frying, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'ground sirloin'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, finely chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Italian seasoning'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'marinara sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'whole milk'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded mozzarella cheese'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '⅛', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'whole-milk ricotta cheese'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh basil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped fresh flat-leaf parsley'}
steps: Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook lasagna noodles in the boiling water, stirring occasionally, until tender yet firm to the bite, about 8 minutes. Drain and pat dry with paper towels. Cut each noodle into assorted desired shapes.. Pour vegetable oil to a depth of 3 inches into a Dutch oven; heat over high to reach 360 degrees F (182 degrees C). Add 8 to 10 pasta pieces, one at a time to avoid them sticking together, and cook, lightly tapping under the oil and stirring with a spider tool occasionally, until golden brown and crispy, 2 to 3 minutes. Remove using a spider or tongs to a paper towel-lined sheet tray, and sprinkle with salt. Repeat with remaining pasta pieces, allowing oil temperature to reach back to 360 degrees F (182 degrees C) before adding next batch.. Set an oven rack in the top third and preheat the oven's broiler. Line a large rimmed baking sheet with foil.. Heat a medium nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add olive oil and ground sirloin; cook, stirring occasionally, until beef is browned, about 3 minutes. Add garlic and Italian seasoning; cook stirring constantly, until fragrant, 1 minute more. Stir in marinara sauce and remove from heat. Set aside.. Melt butter in a small saucepan over medium heat. Whisk in flour and cook, whisking constantly, until starting to bubble, about 30 seconds. Slowly whisk in milk, whisking constantly. Cook over medium heat, whisking often, until slightly thickened, about 2 to 3 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in mozzarella, Parmesan, and remaining 1/8 teaspoon salt.. Arrange lasagna chips in an even layer on the prepared baking sheet. Drizzle 1/2 of the cheese sauce over top and evenly sprinkle with the sirloin mixture. Dollop with ricotta.. Broil in the preheated oven until ricotta gets brown in spots, about 2 minutes. Serve drizzled with remaining cheese sauce, basil, and parsley.
